# Quiz — two attempts per question (FROZEN BEHAVIOUR)

When editing quiz **gameplay / answer-handling logic** (not question content):

## Required behaviour

1. **Two tries per question** — On the first wrong answer, the player stays on the **same question** and gets another chance. Toast: `Wrong answer! One more try.`
2. **Level fails on the second wrong answer** — Only after the **second** wrong attempt on that question should **Game Over / level restart** trigger.
3. **Reset attempts on new question** — Wrong-attempt counter resets when advancing to the next question or restarting the level.

## Scope — all quiz categories EXCEPT Squad Predictor

Applies to every quiz game page, including:

- `src/pages/Game.tsx` (world-cup, guess-who, guess-scoreline, missing-player questions, country-history, world-cup-bingo, etc.)
- `src/pages/PlayerGame.tsx`
- `src/pages/WinnersGame.tsx`
- `src/pages/StadiumsGame.tsx`
- `src/pages/ScorelineGame.tsx`
- `src/pages/ManagersGame.tsx`
- `src/pages/MissingPlayerGame.tsx`
- `src/pages/GuessTheScorerGame.tsx`

**Never change this for 2026 Squad Predictor** — `src/pages/SquadPredictor*.tsx`, `SquadTab.tsx`, `SquadPredictorHubContext.tsx`, and related squad-predictor routes are **out of scope**.

## Source of truth

- Shared constant: `QUIZ_ATTEMPTS_PER_QUESTION = 2` in `src/lib/quizLevelRules.ts`
- Helper: `shouldFailQuizLevelAfterWrong(wrongAttempts)`

Use these helpers when adding or fixing wrong-answer handling — do not hard-code a single-strike fail.

## Never do

- Revert to **one-strike** level failure on first wrong answer
- Change **questions, answers, hints, or option text**
- Touch **2026 Squad Predictor** logic, data, or UI
- Refactor unrelated gameplay (scoring, hints, timers, completion rules) unless explicitly asked

## Definition of done

A quiz gameplay edit is correct only if:

- [ ] First wrong answer retries the same question (no game over)
- [ ] Second wrong answer on that question shows game over / restart
- [ ] Squad Predictor untouched
- [ ] No question/answer data changed
